  "original_title": "\u0dc3\u0dd4\u0dc5\u0dd4 \u0dc4\u0dcf \u0db8\u0db0\u0dca\u200d\u0dba \u0db4\u0dbb\u0dd2\u0db8\u0dcf\u0dab \u0dc0\u0dca\u200d\u0dba\u0dcf\u0db4\u0dcf\u0dbb\u0dd2\u0d9a\u0dba\u0db1\u0dca\u0da7 \u0dc0\u0dd0\u0da9\u0db8\u0dd4\u0dc5\u0dd4\u0dc0\u0d9a\u0dca",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "A workshop for small and medium businesses",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Ceylon Bank in collaboration with the Small and Medium Business Center of the Ceylon Chamber of Commerce and the Chartered Institute of Management Accountants (CIMA) has held a special workshop for small and medium businesses in Puttala.",
        "Believing that businesses belonging to this category are the lifeblood of the country's economy, the bank has taken steps to provide them with the proper guidance they need, and therefore has worked to provide the necessary knowledge and financial solutions to those businesses.",
        "As another step, they are currently working to hold a series of workshops covering the entire island.",
        "The workshop held in Puttalam area was chaired by Mr. Channa Gunawardena, Chief Executive Officer of Dankotuwa Porsilen Company, and discussed customer grouping, branding and its importance, marketing and its challenges, the need for technology and digitization, planning and working in accordance with those plans, and financial solutions. Key areas covered there.",
        "Representatives of various businesses representing sectors like agriculture, trade, information technology, salt production, spice export, garments, dry goods and construction participated in the workshop. This was the third workshop in this series of workshops, previously held in Ratnapura and Anuradhapura.",
        "The Ceylon Chamber of Commerce, together with the Institute of Chartered Management Accountants, organizes these regional workshops under the theme 'Forward Together'. The primary objective of this has been to enhance the knowledge, skills and financial and technical understanding of small and medium scale businesses in Sri Lanka. 45% of the jobs in this country are generated by businesses in this category, and the 'Forward Together' program was started with the aim of creating a positive impact on the country's economy as a whole by developing those businesses."
      ],
